---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Accessibility Statement" description="News Lancashire accessibility statement. We aim to make local news accessible to everyone.">
  <section class="hero" style="padding-bottom: 1rem;">
    <h1 class="hero-headline">Accessibility</h1>
  </section>
  <div class="article-body">
    <p>
      News Lancashire is committed to making local news accessible to everyone.
      This site is designed to meet WCAG 2.1 Level AA standards.
    </p>
    <h2>What we do</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Semantic HTML throughout (headings, landmarks, lists)</li>
      <li>Skip-to-content link on every page</li>
      <li>High contrast dark theme (minimum 4.5:1 ratio)</li>
      <li>Keyboard-navigable interface</li>
      <li>Focus indicators on all interactive elements</li>
      <li>Descriptive link text and ARIA labels</li>
      <li>Responsive design that works at any zoom level</li>
      <li>No auto-playing media</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Feedback</h2>
    <p>
      If you encounter an accessibility issue, please contact us. We take accessibility
      seriously and will address reported issues promptly.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
